cAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}",{"title":33,"searchDepth":62,"depth":62,"links":755},[756,757,758],{"id":14,"depth":62,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":62,"text":23},{"id":738,"depth":62,"text":739},"JavaScript","2020-08-08 22:48:42","Time to talk about passing objects by reference. If you don't get how reference semantics work in JavaScript, it's really easy to step on a landmine. We'll walk through call by value vs call by reference, why changing one variable can secretly change another, and the simplest way to spot when reference behavior is in play.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002Fjavascript-core-26-object-reference-semantics",{"title":6,"description":761},false,"en\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-core-26-object-reference-semantics",[759,770,771],"JavaScript Core","Object",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F08\u002F08\u002Fjavascript-core-26-object-reference-semantics\u002F","thPkMM8_4wumbq1sV3KODI0TbGdf2DAHm-xVl83wM4o",{"newer":776,"older":780},{"url":777,"title":778,"date":779},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F08\u002F10\u002Fpixijs-v5-27-crop-sprite-texture\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (27) - Cropping Images with Rectangle and Texture","2020-08-10 08:34:32",{"url":781,"title":782,"date":783},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F08\u002F08\u002Fjavascript-core-25-object-undefined-property-default\u002F","JavaScript Core (25): Why Reading a Missing Object Property Gives You undefined (and Sometimes Crashes)","2020-08-08 21:28:14",[785,790,795],{"url":786,"title":787,"date":788,"readingMinutes":789},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2026\u002F03\u002F10\u002Fweb-crypto-api-encryption-guide\u002F","No crypto Package, No Node.js — The Web Crypto API Does It All in the Browser","2026-03-10 09:45:08","9",{"url":791,"title":792,"date":793,"readingMinutes":794},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F08\u002Fjquery-why-it-declined\u002F","jQuery Was Once King — So Why Did It Fall Off?","2025-12-08 21:35:24","7",